import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['Miles_per_Gallon'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    cylinder_counts = data['Cylinders'].value_counts()
    cylinder_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Cylinders')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Cylinders?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    origin_counts = data['Origin'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(origin_counts, labels=origin_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of Origin?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
